    "body": "### Problem\n\nif `vim.opt.shellslash` is true, neovim recognizes path delimiter as '/'\r\nso the result of `vim.fn.expand()` use slash instead of backslash in windows. \r\nbut The `vim.api.nvim_buf_get_name()` doesn't be applied.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. open nvim\r\n2. set `vim.opt.shellslash = true`\r\n3. see `lua =vim.api.nvim_buf_get_name(buf_id)`\r\n4. see `lua =vim.fn.expand('%:p')\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nDelimiter of result of `vim.api.nvim_buf_get_name()` changes to slash when User set `vim.opt.shellslash` true\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.10.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim doesn't have nvim_buf_get_name function\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 10\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm 20240203-110809-5046fc22\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nscoop",
